==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from Greek '''oecumenopolis''', meaning "world city."  Coined by [[Greek]] [[city]] planner [[w:Constantinos Doxiadis|Constantinos Doxiadis]] in 1967.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''ecumenopolis'''

#A worldwide or planetwide city.

